---
import Base from "../layouts/base.astro";
import NormalBlock from "../components/normal_block.astro";

const metadata = {
    title: "Privacy Notice",
    description: "Detailed information on how I handle and protect your data. Learn about your rights concerning data privacy.",
    type: "article",
};
---

<Base metadata={metadata}>
    <article>
        <h2 class="py-4 md:py-6 font-lora text-xl md:text-4xl max-w-[75%] mx-auto text-center">Privacy Notice</h2>
        <NormalBlock title="Last updated: January 2026">
            <p class="">This Privacy Notice explains how I collect, use and protect your personal data when you use my services, in accordance with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="1. Who I am">
            <p class="mb-2">I am the data controller responsible for your personal data.</p>
            <p class=""><strong>Business name:</strong> Aniko Boleradszkine Bolyos (sole trader)</p>
            <p class=""><strong>Location:</strong> United Kingdom</p>
            <p class=""><strong>Email:</strong> anikobolyos89@gmail.com</p>
            <p class=""><strong>Telephone:</strong> 0785 797 8600</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="2. What personal data I collect">
            <p class="">Depending on the service you use, I may collect the following types of personal data:</p>

            <h4 class="mt-3 md:mt-6">a) Contact and identification data</h4>
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5">
                <li>Name</li>
                <li>Email address</li>
                <li>Telephone number</li>
                <li>Postal address</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 class="mt-3 md:mt-6">b) Service-related information (style consultancy)</h4>
            <p class="">Collected via a Google Form for services such as colour analysis, wardrobe editing, body shape analysis and personal shopping:</p>
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5 mb-1 md:mb-3">
                <li>Clothing preferences and lifestyle information</li>
                <li>Colour analysis results</li>
                <li>Body shape–related information (for styling purposes only)</li>
                <li>Wardrobe-related notes and observations</li>
                <li>Shopping and style preferences</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="">These responses are stored securely in a Google Spreadsheet and are only retained until the relevant service has been fully completed.</p>

            <h4 class="mt-3 md:mt-6">c) Colour interpretation / colour psychology services</h4>
            <p class="">For colour interpretation services, I may also collect:</p>
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5 mb-1 md:mb-3">
                <li>Date of birth (used solely for numerology-based colour interpretation)</li>
                <li>Notes created before the consultation</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="">These notes are used only during the consultation process and are deleted afterwards.</p>

            <h4 class="mt-3 md:mt-6">d) Photographs (optional)</h4>
            <p class="">With your explicit consent, I may take photographs of outfits or wardrobes for consultation purposes only.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="3. How I use your personal data">
            <p class="">I use your personal data to:</p>
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5 mb-1 md:mb-3">
                <li>Provide and deliver my services</li>
                <li>Prepare personalised style, colour and wardrobe advice</li>
                <li>Communicate with you before, during and after the service</li>
                <li>Arrange appointments</li>
                <li>Issue invoices and comply with accounting and tax obligations</li>
                <li>Maintain basic client records</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="">I do not use your data for automated decision-making or profiling.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="4. Lawful basis for processing">
            <p class="">Under UK GDPR, I rely on the following lawful bases:</p>
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5 mb-1 md:mb-3">
                <li><strong>Contract:</strong> to provide the services you request and to manage bookings and payments</li>
                <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> to retain invoicing and accounting records</li>
                <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> basic client administration and communication</li>
                <li><strong>Explicit consent:</strong>
                    <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5">
                        <li>for colour interpretation and numerology-based analysis</li>
                        <li>for taking and using photographs</li>
                        <li>for any optional information you choose to provide</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="">You may withdraw your consent at any time.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="5. How long I keep your data">
            <p class="">I retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to provide my services and comply with legal obligations. Specifically:</p>
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5 mb-1 md:mb-3">
                <li>Contact and invoicing data (name, address, email, phone number): <strong>6 years</strong>, to comply with UK accounting and tax regulations</li>
                <li>Style consultation form responses and notes: <strong>deleted once the service has been completed</strong></li>
                <li>Colour interpretation notes: <strong>deleted after the consultation</strong> or provided to you upon request</li>
                <li>Photographs: <strong>deleted after the service</strong>, unless you request otherwise</li>
            </ul>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="6. How your data is stored">
            <p class="">Your data is stored securely using trusted service providers, including:</p>
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5 mb-1 md:mb-3">
                <li>Google Forms and Google Sheets (for service questionnaires and temporary storage)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="">I take reasonable steps to ensure your data is protected and accessed only when necessary.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="7. Sharing your data">
            <p class="">I do not sell or rent your personal data. I may share limited data with:</p>
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5 mb-1 md:mb-3">
                <li>My accountant or bookkeeper (for legal and tax purposes only)</li>
                <li>Service providers acting as data processors (e.g. email, invoicing or cloud storage services)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="">All third parties are required to process your data in compliance with UK GDPR.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="8. International data transfers">
            <p class="">Some of the tools I use (such as Google services) may process data outside the UK. Where this happens, appropriate safeguards are in place in accordance with UK GDPR requirements.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="9. Your data protection rights">
            <p class="">You have the right to:</p>
            <ul class="list-outside list-disc relative left-4 md:left-5 mb-1 md:mb-3">
                <li>Access your personal data</li>
                <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
                <li>Restrict or object to processing</li>
                <li>Request data portability</li>
                <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="">You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the UK Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO): <a href="https://www.ico.org.uk">https://www.ico.org.uk</a></p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="10. Is providing data mandatory?">
            <p class="">Providing basic contact and invoicing data is necessary to receive my services. All other information is optional but may be required to deliver personalised advice.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="11. Disclaimer – personal interpretation">
            <p class="">Any colour analysis, styling advice or numerology-based interpretation is provided for personal styling and self-development purposes only. It does not constitute medical, psychological or therapeutic advice.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="12. Changes to this Privacy Notice">
            <p class="">I may update this Privacy Notice from time to time. The latest version will always be available on my website.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
    </article>
</Base>
